node.text:
Trying to use the small platform I have to raise awareness to something I will forever stand against. 
His name was George Floyd. He was unarmed. 
The cop who killed him is now standing trial for murder - as he should be, but the three who watched by as a man knelt on his neck until he died and did nothing are yet to be arrested. 
This is yet another horrific case of police brutality, and violence against people of color. 
This horrific thing doesn't end in america.
The subject is close to home for me, and I'm certain it is for many others. 
Justice must be served. I hope someday we could live in a world in which such horrible things are the stuff of horror fiction and those only. 
#justiceforgeorgefloyd #blacklivesmatter
#acab

"If you were to look at a crai straight ahead, they would not seem so distant to you from your human self. 
They are tall, surely, but some humans are lanky.
Their skin, either pale and pearly or dark and cold-looking, could, in some lightings- resemble the skin of a human. 
Their ears could be covered by the traditional long hair they kept, and their purple, blue, green or grey eyes could be explained away as genes. 
Their legs seem odd, but you wouldn't have noticed under their puffed pants and costume made boots. 
The crai, from a straight forward point of view, 
Seem like they could just almost pass off as sharp-featured humans,

But that is far from the truth. 
Were you to look by the side of them, you would see the lanky body,  twisted and odd,
Their legs looking like the hooves of a goat standing like a human, their arms too long to be balanced, their ribs popping forward even on the fattest of them. 
Were you to catch one running, or climbing up on rocky mountains, you would see their legs move in an inhuman fashion, fast and odd. 
It would read as wrong, if you were not to be neighbors with them for so long.  Their faces, long and sharp, could seem nearly soft in some lights,
And under robes their women would look like proper princesses, and under armour, the men like godly heros or magical knights.
The crai were not humans, but they must've been far more People than any human I've encountered." #digitalart #art #digitaldrawing #drawing #digitalpainting #painting #digitalillustration #illustration #digitalillustrator #illustrator #digitalsketch #sketch #digital #photoshop #artistsofig

"There is something terrible about to happen. "Promise me you'll be back."
His hand was clasped in mine and I refused to let him go.
I knew what awaited him. I knew death is soon to come. 
I could smell it in the air.
The silver eyed goddess stood in front of us, 
unmoved. 
Unfeeling. 
She did not see him as a challenge. 
His eyes burnt with the passion for fight and he let go of my hand. "Samuel. Promise me."
He looked at me and did not say a word.
